dReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=148.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.zgeek.com/images/topics/skul1.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Promotions?</span><hr size=1> I shall support each of the level 20 crowd I have grouped with each of you and have seen your skill put to good use, For King For Country.<br><br>Now all you need is one more knight approval and then the consent of Yumpin Yuber... Err I mean Knight Captain of the Every growing army of Paladins Yuber. (for Persaunt, and Baeley)<br><br>Mistress Zannah for K. and Riggs<br><br>and Edare for Ral. and Caron.<br><br>When these are met you shall join the rank of Keeper.<br><br>As for your second concern, expressing feelings of doubt about ability to fight against our enimy realms.<br>I have put some thought into this and hope to plan a guild hunt for these Pagans and Demons. This will happen in mid month of January year of our Lord 2002. I will hope to see all attend if possible reguardless of level.<br><br>M.<br>Forgotten Grail Keepers<br>Knight Errant<br>Wizard of Albion <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub31.ezboard.com/ubaeley.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Baeley</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#993300>(12/21/01 10:05:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub31.ezboard.com/fforgottengrailkeepersfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=148.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Promotions?</span><hr size=1> Aye, I been wonderin' 'bout this fer a few days meself. Havent seen Sir Yuber in some time, and now I cannah find the post describing whats required to become a Keeper. <br><br>I'm sure I'll find Sir Yuber at some point, but if somebody could point me at the link that has the info on what the requirements are for each rank, I'll smite 'em a Pagan er two.<br><br>Thanks fer sponsorin' us Meda. Yer not as bad as Gwal said you were afterall.<br><br> <p>Baeley Hennesy <BR>Classically trained ta Crookify yer nose, Pagan.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub31.ezboard.com/ukalaz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kalaz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>High Lord God and King</span><br>  Posts: 143<br> <font color=#993300>(12/21/01 10:12:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub31.ezboard.com/fforgottengrailkeepersfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=148.topic&index=3>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://home.twcny.rr.com/blackros/yellowbeard.jpg height=94 width=100></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Promotions?</span><hr size=1> Just a guess here, a wild shot in the dark as it were, but I <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> think</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> (just think, mind you, not know) that the requirements for promotions just might be in the forum called &quot;Promotions&quot;.<br><br>Just a slim possibility there, but you never know....<br><br> <p>--<br><center><img src="http://home.twcny.rr.com/blackros/sig1.gif" border="0"></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub31.ezboard.com/umallagarmisanthrope.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mallagar Misanthrope</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 105<br> <font color=#993300>(12/21/01 10:48:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub31.ezboard.com/fforgottengrailkeepersfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=148.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.zgeek.com/images/topics/skul1.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Promotions?</span><hr size=1> Are you sure about that Kalaz? I coulda sworn our promotion pages where there to talk about and display our new FGK products Like:<br><br>FGK Goo off: magically brewed to get out those tough stains from a hards days fight. Proven to remove Goblin blood, spider ikor, and boogie boogers.<br><br>FGK Crafted Purple blocking sunglasses: Does your friend have a problem? Does he favor the putrescent plumage of the color purple? Tired of nearly going blind each time he runs up on you? Then FGK Purple Blocking sunglasses are for you. With this work of mid-evil Mastery, you will be able to fight for our country again without fear of eye soreness or near dementia.<br>(still working on the name for this one)<br><br>FGK Yumpin Yuber snacks: Sure to put a spring in you step and a leap into your attack. Yumpin Yuber snacks make great stocking stuffers.<br><br>FGK Wizard Repair Kit: Has your wizard been pummeled flat again? Pierced with arrows? Ripped to shreads? Well here's the kit for you. Created by our very own Mistress Zannah. This kit includes:<br><br>12 blood packs (for those especially draining types of wounds)<br><br>13' of reinforced twine (to stitch him back togeather)<br><br>1 billows air pump For those hard hits that leave em flat<br><br>144 clean silk swatches (to stuff in the holes the arrows leave while passing through their frail frame)<br><br>1 reusable hemp sack (when it's just to bothersome to deal with the pieces right then)<br><br>and one broom and dustpan (to make sure you clean up everything)<br><br><br>These and much more can be found on our promotions pages.<br><br>:P<br><br>M.<br>Dem Henessey they can fight all right. But not to much on the thinking. At least they have Khay to look out for em.<br> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub31.ezboard.com/umallagarmisanthrope.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mallagar Misanthrope</A> at: 12/21/01 10:52:09 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub31.ezboard.com/usulyen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sulyen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>cRaZy Edare's<br>Armor Emporium!</span><br>  Posts: 211<br> <font color=#993300>(12/21/01 11:17:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub31.ezboard.com/fforgottengrailkeepersfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=148.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Promotions?</span><hr size=1> If you are an armsman and meet the promotion requirements.  Please post a request for promotion (in the promotions forum) and a few times in-game that you will be online. Or give me a tell in game. <br><br>Also, if you have questions on the requirements, post as well.<br> <p><br><hr>Sulyen, 54th Pathfinder,Ravens Wings,Tribunal<br>Edare, 34th Armsman, Forgotten Grail Keepers, Guinevere<br><br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub31.ezboard.com/ubaeley.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Baeley</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#993300>(12/22/01 11:24:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub31.ezboard.com/fforgottengrailkeepersfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=148.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Promotions?</span><hr size=1> Ya know, yer probably right. The promotions forum, Aye. Good place ta check that sorta thing isnt it. <br><br>Only problem Mr. Funnybones is I dinnah have access to it. Haven't for about a month er so now. So, since ya decided ta be a wiseass 'bout it all, here' me solution.<br><br>Meda: Crookified Nose. Done.<br><br>Gwal: I'll bash yer Helm in till it looks like slag. Then I'm gonna turn it round and round so yer neck is all twisty like. Last, i'm gonna crookify yer kilt and turn ya loose round Elbb.<br><br>Edare: Buy ya an ale and resist the urge ta crookify ya, even tho ya still think I'm an Armsman =). <p>Baeley Hennesy <BR>Classically trained ta Crookify yer nose, Pagan.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub31.ezboard.com/upersaunt.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Persaunt</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#993300>(12/22/01 4:50:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub31.ezboard.com/fforgottengrailkeepersfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=148.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Promotions?</span><hr size=1> It seems that by guildline number 7 that we would not have to jump through these hoops to get promoted to something higher than recruit.  We were all in either Raven's Wings or Ebon Rose on Tribunal.  Most of us were officers in one or the other (or even guild leaders - elbb of ER).  So I guess the question is, what does &quot;appropriate rank&quot; mean, since that is not clearly defined.  I, for one, would not take that to mean recruit because  if it did, the &quot;appropriate rank&quot; would not have to be mentioned at all - It would just be &quot;...invited into the guild.&quot;  So far, it seems most of that people who are at rank Knight and above have the same qualifying factors as we do (under rule 7), and yet we are still recruits.  The only difference being, we were not there at the time of guild creation (since we were not told until after the fact).  <br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub31.ezboard.com/ukalaz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kalaz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>High Lord God and King</span><br>  Posts: 144<br> <font color=#993300>(12/22/01 7:24:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub31.ezboard.com/fforgottengrailkeepersfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=148.topic&index=8>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://home.twcny.rr.com/blackros/yellowbeard.jpg height=94 width=100></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Promotions?</span><hr size=1> You probably should have been invited as Keepers and would therefoer be up for promotion to Knight after 30 days.  Talk to your sponsor, check with the class leader.   Not a real big deal from what I can see.<br><br>Oh, and Baeley, unless you changed your account info sometime in the recent past, you've had access to those forums for a while.  Possible that ezboard screwed up the access or something, but from everything I can see you guys should both have access.  If it's still not working, the only thing I can do is suggest you make a new account and get us the name and we'll enable access for that one as well.<br><br> <p>--<br><center><img src="http://home.twcny.rr.com/blackros/sig1.gif" border="0"></center></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub31.ezboard.com/fforgottengrailkeepersfrm8.showPrevMessage?topicID=148.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub31.ezboard.com/fforgottengrailkeepersfrm8.showNextMessage?topicID=148.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub31.ezboard.com/fforgottengrailkeepersfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=148.topic&index=8><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/classic/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http